<subSubSection id="39CBB18F9024640BFF3C873DFE59B385" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="716EE2049024640BFF3C873DFE59B385" blockId="3.[192,1440,321,506]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="43A53E169024640BFF3C873DFECFB326" bold="true" box="[192,336,321,345]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B6D199879024640BFEAA873EFDE9B326" authorityName="Woodley" authorityYear="2015" box="[342,630,322,346]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Paraberismyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitator">
<emphasis id="43A53E169024640BFEAA873EFDE9B326" box="[342,630,322,346]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Paraberismyia imitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other species in the genus by having the abdomen uniformly brown, without yellowish areas medially on tergites (
<figureCitation id="E9EAFE819024640BFB93871EFB4CB305" box="[1135,1235,354,378]" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="5.[192,288,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,685,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-104@5.[192,1440,685,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1–3. Holotype male of Paraberismyia imitator, n. sp. 1) Dorsal habitus view. 2) Left lateral habitus view (mirror image). 3) Anterior view of head. Figure 4. Male of Berismyia fusca Giglio-Tos. 4) Anterior view of head." pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 1, 2</figureCitation>
). In my previous key (
<bibRefCitation id="15409FF59024640BFF0787FEFE46B3E5" author="Woodley, N. E." box="[251,473,386,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="25 - 45" refId="ref2960" refString="Woodley, N. E. 2013. A revision of the Neotropical genus Paraberismyia Woodley (Diptera, Stratiomyidae, Beridinae) with three new species. ZooKeys 353: 25 - 45." type="journal article" year="2013">Woodley 2013: 27</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="B6D199879024640BFE1387FEFDE9B3E6" authorityName="Woodley" authorityYear="2015" box="[495,630,386,409]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Paraberismyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitator">
<emphasis id="43A53E169024640BFE1387FEFDE9B3E6" box="[495,630,386,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">P. imitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will not key to any species because at couplet 2, while cell cu 
<emphasis id="43A53E169024640BFA8F87FEFA1DB3E6" box="[1395,1410,386,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">p</emphasis>
is completely covered with microtrichia, the first tarsomere of the hind leg is completely pale so one cannot proceed to couplet 3. Thus, the key could be modified so that at couplet 1, when choosing “males” it leads to couplet 1a:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="39CBB18F9024640BFF3C845EFA3FB006" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="key">
<paragraph id="716EE2049024640BFF3C845EFE99B045" blockId="3.[192,262,546,570]" box="[192,262,546,570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
